<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/1685a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-21T16:00:00-05:00">October 21, 1937—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>111. Your despatch 2994 August 19, 1936, annex 2.<note n="14" xml:id="d243fn14">Annex not printed; for an extract from the
                                    despatch, see <ref target="frus1936v02#pg_201"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1936, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 201</ref>.</note> Ascertain if practicable
                                and cable confidential information regarding rumored decree that
                                German Jews will not be permitted to leave or return to Germany.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>